{# Decoy landing page для Caddy-fronted webtunnel (anti-censorship P1 #3).

   Threat model: а VAS-class active probe issues а plain HTTP GET / к
   veil's `:443` listener.  Прежде это hit veil's webtunnel
   handler which served а tiny one-paragraph default decoy ("Server
   status / All systems operational") — clearly machine-generated и
   thin enough к flag as "не real site".

   With Caddy in front, the probe instead lands on this template.
   Properties chosen to pass "looks like an ordinary small static
   site" heuristics:

   * Multi-page (links к /about, /sitemap.xml, /robots.txt)
   * External CSS reference (loaded inline для simplicity, but
     looks как normal site structure)
   * Plain-English content без obvious veil/proxy references
   * No JavaScript (some sites are static-only; не а red flag)
   * Standard semantic HTML5 structure

   Operators are encouraged to replace this template с а real
   snapshot of а small static site (open-source project landing,
   personal blog, etc.) — anything с real content и historical
   substance is harder к distinguish от а live decoy.

   Variable: `decoy_site_name` — operator-configurable, defaults к
   а generic placeholder.
-#}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>{{ decoy_site_name | default('Notes &amp; Drafts') }}</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <meta name="description" content="Working notes, drafts, и occasional longer-form writing.">
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://{{ veil_host }}/">
    <link rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" title="RSS" href="/feed.xml">
    <style>
        * { box-sizing: border-box; }
        body {
            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #2c2c2c;
            max-width: 720px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
            background: #fdfdfd;
        }
        h1 { font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
        h2 { font-weight: 600; margin-top: 2.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e5e5; padding-bottom: 0.25rem; }
        nav { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e5e5; }
        nav a { margin-right: 1.5rem; color: #555; text-decoration: none; }
        nav a:hover { color: #000; text-decoration: underline; }
        article { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
        article time { color: #888; font-size: 0.875rem; }
        article h3 { margin-bottom: 0.25rem; font-weight: 500; }
        a.read-more { font-size: 0.875rem; color: #0066cc; }
        footer { margin-top: 4rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid #e5e5e5; color: #888; font-size: 0.875rem; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>{{ decoy_site_name | default('Notes &amp; Drafts') }}</h1>
        <p>Working notes, drafts, и occasional longer-form writing.</p>
    </header>

    <nav>
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/about.html">About</a>
        <a href="/feed.xml">RSS</a>
    </nav>

    <h2>Recent</h2>

    <article>
        <h3>On choosing the right level of abstraction</h3>
        <time datetime="2026-04-12">12 April 2026</time>
        <p>
            One of the most useful skills in software design is knowing
            when к invent а new layer и when к stay close к the metal.
            А good rule of thumb: если you find yourself repeatedly
            translating between two representations, the boundary is
            probably misplaced…
        </p>
    </article>

    <article>
        <h3>Notes on small-team incident response</h3>
        <time datetime="2026-03-28">28 March 2026</time>
        <p>
            После а few rough on-call weeks I started keeping а short
            "what worked / what didn't" checklist.  The single biggest
            lesson: blameless retro is not optional — it's the cheapest
            way к build the kind of trust that lets people surface
            problems early.
        </p>
    </article>

    <article>
        <h3>Reading log: March</h3>
        <time datetime="2026-03-15">15 March 2026</time>
        <p>
            А mix of fiction и technical reading this month.  Highlights:
            а new edition of Hennessy &amp; Patterson, а short essay
            collection by Maciej Cegłowski, и the second half of <em>The
            Master and Margarita</em> (took my time с the Pevear/Volokhonsky
            translation).
        </p>
    </article>

    <footer>
        <p>Built с Hugo · Hosted on а small VPS · No tracking, no ads.</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
